           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$checkbox_mc = new_checkbox_multiple_choice();
$checkbox_mc -> qa("Which of the following statements correctly provides a practical interpretation of the composite function \( f(h(t)) \) ?  Select all that apply if more than one is appropriate.",
                   "The area of the circle at time $BITALIC t $EITALIC.",
                   "The area of a circle which at time \( t \) has radius 
                    \( h(t) \) .");

$checkbox_mc -> extra("The length of the radius of a circle with area 
                       \( A = f(r) \) at time \( t \) . ",
               "At what time \( t \) the area will be \( A = f(r) \) .",
               "The length of the radius at time \( t \) .",
               "At what time \( t \) the radius will be \( r = h(t) \) .");
                      
$checkbox_mc -> makeLast("None of the above");

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 18:
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
Let \( A = f(r) \) be the area of a circle with radius \( r \) and \( r = h(t) \) be the radius of the circle at time \( t \).
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
\{ $checkbox_mc -> print_q \}
$BR
\{ $checkbox_mc -> print_a \}
$BR

END_TEXT

ANS(checkbox_cmp( $checkbox_mc -> correct_ans ));

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR 
The function \( f(h(t)) \) gives the area of the circle as a function of time, \( t \).  The value \( h(t) \) denotes the radius of the circle at this time.
$BR
END_SOLUTION

